From a670ef54f601796157986cdaf5b78513322f616c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
Date: Fri, 15 May 2026 17:41:05 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 572/586] AOSCOS: drm: cix: make sure fixed-length array
 doesn't get variable lengths

When building with CONFIG_WERROR, the following error occurs:

  drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_wb_connector.c:281:35: error: argument to variable-length array is too large [-Werror=vla-larger-than=]
    281 |         struct drm_prop_enum_list enum_list[max_t(int, DRM_COLOR_ENCODING_MAX,
        |                                   ^~~~~~~~~

Use MAX_T macro to correctly define this array.

Fixes: "CIXTECH: drm: add cix linlon dp driver"
Link: https://github.com/cixtech/cix-linux-main/issues/26
Suggested-by: Xinhui Yang <cyan@cyano.uk>
Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_wb_connector.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_wb_connector.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_wb_connector.c
index 82b9efdcd42cb..8380a14f30987 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_wb_connector.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_wb_connector.c
@@ -278,7 +278,7 @@ linlondp_wb_connector_create_color_prop(struct linlondp_wb_connector *wb_conn)
 {
 	struct drm_device *dev = wb_conn->base.base.dev;
 	struct drm_property *prop;
-	struct drm_prop_enum_list enum_list[max_t(int, DRM_COLOR_ENCODING_MAX,
+	struct drm_prop_enum_list enum_list[MAX_T(int, DRM_COLOR_ENCODING_MAX,
 						  DRM_COLOR_RANGE_MAX)];
 	u32 supported_encoding = BIT(DRM_COLOR_YCBCR_BT601) |
 				 BIT(DRM_COLOR_YCBCR_BT709);
-- 
2.52.0

